{
  "text": "The action of global space-time translation on (3.1) was studied in [CITATION_1] . The two dimensional field φ h,h (z,z) is the restriction of the three dimensional field φ h,h (u, z,z) to the u = 0 celestial sphere. Correlation function of the three dimensional fields φ h,h (u, z,z) is defined as [CITATION_2] ,",
  "correct_citation": {
